he best examples of the poet who is true to his art as determined by his innermost impulses. His poetry has fertilized a whole generation of writers in Spanish America and in Spain, and even now his influence continues to be felt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aEnguídanos, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlorit, Eugenio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzalez-Gerth, Miguel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aImbert, Enrique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRioseco, Arturo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchade, George D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchade, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311074535140uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/70054340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292772953423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292772953/original  a978-3-11-074535-1  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles